gov.nih.nlm.ling.wrappers

Class CoreNLPWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.nlm.ling.wrappers.CoreNLPWrapper

  • public class CoreNLPWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    A class that provides access to Stanford CoreNLP functionality.

    Ideally, we should be able to access each CoreNLP annotation type separately, but, in general, we assume that we have token, sentence, lemma, part-of-speech, parse tree and dependency information before we can do anything, so currently we are performing all these operations at once.

    The annotation types are read from a Properties object, which should contain annotators as key and a comma-delimited list of annotator types (by default, we use tokenize,ssplit,pos,lemma,parse as the annotators).

    Author:
    Halil Kilicoglu
